{"atom_id": "md_dmDA_assn_a002", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "file": "knowledge_base/domains/DA/assumptions.md", "line_start": 3, "line_end": 3, "verbatim": "1. This domain records the amount of study product transferred to or from the study subject.", "parent_section": "§DA [DA — Assumptions]", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "general-purpose", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_md_v1.9.1", "ts": "2026-05-06T02:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "md_dmDA_assn_a003", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "file": "knowledge_base/domains/DA/assumptions.md", "line_start": 4, "line_end": 4, "verbatim": "   a. Transfers of devices are not represented in this domain, but in the Device Tracking and Disposition (DT) domain. See the SDTMIG for Medical Devices (available at https://www.cdisc.org/standards/foundational/medical-devices-sdtmig/).", "parent_section": "§DA [DA — Assumptions]", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "general-purpose", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_md_v1.9.1", "ts": "2026-05-06T02:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "md_dmDA_assn_a004", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "file": "knowledge_base/domains/DA/assumptions.md", "line_start": 5, "line_end": 5, "verbatim": "   b. For drugs, transfers are usually recorded using the tests \"Dispensed Amount\" and \"Returned Amount\".", "parent_section": "§DA [DA — Assumptions]", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "general-purpose", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_md_v1.9.1", "ts": "2026-05-06T02:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "md_dmDA_assn_a005", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "file": "knowledge_base/domains/DA/assumptions.md", "line_start": 6, "line_end": 6, "verbatim": "   c. Test terminology for other products may be different; for example, for nutrition, the tests might be \"Prepared Amount\" and \"Unused Amount\".", "parent_section": "§DA [DA — Assumptions]", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "general-purpose", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_md_v1.9.1", "ts": "2026-05-06T02:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "md_dmDA_assn_a006", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "file": "knowledge_base/domains/DA/assumptions.md", "line_start": 8, "line_end": 8, "verbatim": "2. DACAT may be used to differentiate transfers of different groups of products (e.g., rescue medications vs. investigational medications).", "parent_section": "§DA [DA — Assumptions]", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "general-purpose", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_md_v1.9.1", "ts": "2026-05-06T02:00:00Z"}}
